      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">4/6/79 ¶  ¶ This day, dear Dr Balfour, I received already a copy of the new transactions of the Bot. Soc. of Edinburgh, in which your ¶  ¶ splendid ¶  ¶ paper on the Halophilas is contained. ¶ J.Balfo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.06.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Bayley<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Balfour</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh, I. B. Balfour correspondence.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4/6/79</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day, dear Dr Balfour, I received already a copy of the new transactions of the Bot. Soc. of Edinburgh, in which your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">splendid</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>paper on the Halophilas is contained.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Balfour (1879).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>So I need not trouble you for sending me a copy of your valuable memoir, unless indeed you have a separate print for my own priv. library to spare. I see now, that the male flower of H. spinulosa (Ascherson) are also as yet unknown to you, and I must make once more efforts to obtain them. As Mr<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-size: 10pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Bentham did not mention, that I placed H. spinulosa into<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Hydrocharideae</hi>
               </seg>, you seem to have remained unaware of the fact as you might not have had the particular vol. of the "fragmenta" at hand.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78), vol. 7, p. 182, where he cites B74.08.01, p. 219, in which M considers<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Halophila</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to belong to Najadeae; he also places it there in B75.13.10, p. 91. No reference to a transfer to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>Hydrocharideae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been found in any issue of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg>, but the genus is treated as a member of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hydrocharideae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B83.03.04, p. 115, where the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>citation is B74.08.01, p. 219.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will proceed with the researches on this particular plant so soon as I get<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♂</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>fl., and inform you of the result, begging of you at the same time to keep me posted up in anything that may be written by you on the subject, or anything else that may escape my notice here at so great a distance.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you have not deemed me intrusive in sending you a few recommendatory lines for the successorship to your worthy &amp; venerable fathers position; I feel sure you accepted them in the spirit in which they were offered.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Letter not found</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Kindly let me know, whether your father &amp; yourself like the H. spinulosa dedicated to you as Balfouria, should the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">♂</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>fl. prove it to be a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">well</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>marked genus. Of course you will have seen in my letter, sent a week ago, that I abolished RBr's Balfouria long ago.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Letter not found</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">. See Bentham (1863-78), vol. 4, pp 316-7, where Bentham followed M's herbarium name transfer to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Wrightia</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.. M did not erect another<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Balfouria</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Balfouria</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Halophila<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>spinulosa</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hydrocharideae</p>
         </div>
